000F51r 1  60                   RTS
000F52r 1               
000F52r 1               ; Helper: read one char from file in tmp1, returns it in A (0 if F_EOF set).
000F52r 1               ; Then peeks the next char (loading next sector if needed) and sets F_EOF
000F52r 1               ; when no more data is available — so EOF(F) reflects the correct state
000F52r 1               ; *before* the next READ.  Trashes tmp2, X, Y.  Preserves tmp1, tmp3.
000F52r 1               file_read_char_helper:
000F52r 1  A0 A6                LDY     #F_EOF
000F54r 1  B1 rr                LDA     (tmp1),y
