0014DAr 1               ; Existing files are scanned to EOF using the normal buffered read path so
0014DAr 1               ; F_BUF holds the last sector and F_POS lands at the first CTRL-Z (or 128
0014DAr 1               ; when the file ended on a full sector boundary). For a partial final sector,
0014DAr 1               ; FCB[32] is backed up so the next PEM_WRITE updates that last record first.
